We would like to view dependencies from different fixversions even though we would be filtering on a single release.

Dependencies with different fixversions are filtered out when using a single release in the quick filter. These dependencies should be displayed regardless. This is only needed for incoming dependencies that we require not dependencies that we will be delivering to other people. In that instance the other persons JIRA Portfolio plan would throw up the dependency they have on us.

This is needed because filtering on two fixversions at the same time sometimes results in a very long graphically represented schedule and shows every single thing from the other release rather than just the dependency that is needed

