Need a way to identify a line within Jira Portfolio Backlog, such that a link can be provided to a user, showing the specific line. When Backlog has hundreds of items, it is very difficult to communicate / share with other users.

This could be implemented as a unique, immutable ID on each line. Links could then filter Backlog to show the item with that ID (and its parents).

This is similar to the way in which an individual story has ID / link, e.g. https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPO-176

